        "created_at": "2025-01-22T18:47:04.477Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Sometimes I send a reply to a message and then realize I forgot to quote the message I was replying to, or that my reply would have been clearer if I had quoted a specific message. It would be nice in those cases if you could edit the message and attach a quote after the fact. Currently, on Android, if you attempt to quote a message while editing, it just cancels the reply. (There also seems to be a UI bug where it starts a new message with the quote attached, but doesnâ€™t update the UI to show it, but it you navigate back to the chat list it will show that you have a draft. Going back into the chat will cause it to show up)</p>",
