        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"Herohtar\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"66266\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/48/43780_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Herohtar:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>you can add a link preview to a message after the fact when editing</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I hadnâ€™t realized that as I have link previews off. But the insertion of the preview likely follows a different path than any other attachment since the client does this on its own. What happens if you edit a message that already has a link preview? Can you remove it? Does it remain even if you change the link in the text? If a message is sent with link previews on and generates a preview, then link previews is turned off and the message gets edited, can a link and preview no longer point to the same page?</p>\n<p>I donâ€™t actually mean to request that you test all this out, but there might be a bug somewhere in the link preview - edit message pair.</p>",
